actions.text: The House Committee on Rules reported an original measure, H. Rept. 106-460, by Mr. Goss.

Rule provides for consideration of the conference report to H.R. 1555 with 1 hour of general debate. Previous question shall be considered as ordered without intervening motions except motion to recommit with or without instructions.
Placed on the House Calendar, Calendar No. 153.

official_title: Waiving points of order against the conference report to accompany the bill (H.R. 1555) to authorize appropriations for fiscal year 2000 for intelligence and intelligence-related activities of the United States Government, the Community Management Account, and the Central Intelligence Agency Retirement and Disability System, and for other purposes.

summary.text: Waives points of order against the consideration of the conference report on H.R. 1555 (authorizing appropriations for intelligence and intelligence-related activities).
